advisory.title: Reachable Assertion in grpc
advisory.description: grpc versions before 1.53.0, before 3.2.0, grpcio versions before 1.53.0, io.grpc:grpc-protobuf versions before 1.53.0, Grpc.AspNetCore.Server versions before 2.52.0, and Grpc.Net.Client versions before 2.52.0 are vulnerable to Reachable Assertion causing an `abort()` to be call in gRPC.
advisory.reachableIf: you use any of the following headers via http2 `te: x (x != trailers)`, `:scheme: x (x != http, https)`, or `grpclb_client_stats: x (x == anything)` and a later header is sent that gets the total header size past 8KB

vulns.title: Authorization Bypass Through User-Controlled Key in url-parse

advisory.title: Authorization Bypass Through User-Controlled Key in url-parse
advisory.description:
url-parse prior to version 1.5.8 is vulnerable to Authorization Bypass Through User-Controlled Key. 
This vulnerability occurs due to the `toString()` being unable to determine the correct hostname 
when no port number is provided in the Url. This issue stems from the `toString()` function which
is called by the default export function `Url()`.

cweIds: CWE-639: Authorization Bypass Through User-Controlled Key
